This website serves as a fanpage dedicated to <i>The Odyssey</i>, exploring everything from summaries of the epic to its relevance 
in today''s world. <br>

The goal is to educate and inspire readersâ€”not only to engage with <i>The Odyssey</i> itself, but also to reflect on its deeper 
themes and how they connect to modern societal issues. <br>



This website details information about Homer''s Epic Poem, <i>The Odyssey</i>. Topics that are touched upon in this website, includes:
1. <strong>Introductory Information:</strong> Basic information regarding the story to give a bit of insight into the rest of the 
website and the story itself.
2. <strong>Summary of Text:</strong> A brief summary of the entire twenty-four books that comprise the story of <i>The Odyssey</i>, 
and a brief summary of the events of each twenty-four books.
3. <strong>Themes in Text:</strong> A list comprising most of the themes of <i>The Odyssey</i>, and thematic statements relating to 
the main themes of the story.
4. <strong>Connections to Liturature:</strong> Detailing connections between <i>The Odyssey<i/> and modern literary works, through 
direct retellings of <i>The Odyssey</i> to connections between narrative archetype. Summarizing the story and explaining its 
connection to <i>The Odyssey</i>.
5. <strong>Connection to Societal Issues:</strong> An analyses of connections between certain topics/conflicts in <i>The Odyssey</i>
and modern societal issues, detailing the reflection of societal aspects in <i>The Odyssey</i> and modern society.
6. <strong><i>The Odyssey</i> Paintings:</strong> A small collage of paintings created based on <i>The Odyssey</i>, with their 
corresponding details.
7. <strong>Interesting Facts:</strong> A list of interesting facts about <i>The Odyssey</i>, ranging from details within the story,
details from its creation, etc.